    "updated_at": "2013-08-02T01:24:00Z",
    "body": "Huh. I'm not so sure about this one. Synthesizing or modifying identifiers between source code and compiled form, in general, goes against the grep test (http://jamie-wong.com/2013/07/12/grep-test/) which I generally think of as worth trying to pass. Why not just pass the actual identifier `ALICEBLUE` into the macro?\n",
