    "body": "I think we should just close this pull request.  The conversation between graydon and metajack shows a path towards a alternate (if similar) solution for color names that does not break the grep test: namely, a variant on stringify that downcases.  (Unless someone comes up with a real-world use case that cannot be re-encoded in a reasonable way given that hypothetical `stringify_downcase!` macro.) \n",
